%20Ismail%20Haniyeh%20in%20Tehran%2C%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%2C%20citing%20three%20Iranian%20officials%2C%20briefed%20on%20the%20order%2C%20including%20two%20members%20of%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhamenei%20gave%20the%20order%20at%20an%20emergency%20meeting%20of%20Iran's%20Supreme%20National%20Security%20Council%20on%20Wednesday%20morning%2C%20shortly%20after%20Iran%20announced%20that%20Haniyeh%20had%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20and%20Hamas%20have%20accused%20Israel%20of%20the%20assassination.%20Israel%2C%20which%20is%20at%20war%20with%20Hamas%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20has%20neither%20acknowledged%20nor%20denied%20killing%20Haniyeh%2C%20who%20was%20in%20Tehran%20for%20the%20inauguration%20of%20Iran's%20new%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Israel%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20killing%20enemies%20abroad%2C%20including%20Iranian%20nuclear%20scientists%20and%20military%20commanders%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NYT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20almost%2010%20months%20of%20war%20in%20Gaza%2C%20Iran%20has%20tried%20to%20strike%20a%20balance%2C%20putting%20pressure%20on%20Israel%20with%20sharply%20increased%20attacks%20by%20its%20allies%20and%20proxy%20forces%20in%20the%20region%2C%20while%20avoiding%20an%20all-out%20war%20between%20the%20two%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20biggest%20and%20most%20overt%20attack%20on%20Israel%2C%20Iran%20launched%20hundreds%20of%20missiles%20and%20drones%20in%20April%20in%20retaliation%20for%20an%20Israeli%20strike%20on%20its%20embassy%20compound%20that%20killed%20several%20Iranian%20military%20commanders%20in%20the%20Syrian%20capital%20of%20Damascus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20it%20is%20unclear%20how%20forcefully%20Iran%20will%20respond%2C%20and%20whether%20it%20will%20once%20again%20calibrate%20its%20attack%20to%20steer%20clear%20of%20escalation.%20Iranian%20military%20commanders%20are%20considering%20another%20combination%20attack%20of%20drones%20and%20missiles%20on%20military%20targets%20in%20the%20vicinity%20of%20Tel%20Aviv%20and%20Haifa%2C%20but%20would%20make%20a%20point%20of%20avoiding%20strikes%20on%20civilian%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Iranian%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20option%20under%20consideration%20is%20a%20coordinated%20attack%20from%20Iran%20and%20other%20fronts%20where%20it%20has%20allied%20forces%2C%20including%20Yemen%2C%20Syria%20and%20Iraq%2C%20for%20maximum%20effect%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhamenei%2C%20who%20has%20the%20last%20word%20on%20all%20state%20matters%20and%20is%20also%20the%20commander%20in%20chief%20of%20the%20armed%20forces%2C%20instructed%20military%20commanders%20from%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20and%20the%20army%20to%20prepare%20plans%20for%20both%20an%20attack%20and%20a%20defence%20in%20case%20the%20war%20expands%20and%20Israel%20or%20the%20US%20strike%20Iran%2C%20the%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20public%20statement%20about%20Haniyeh's%20death%2C%20Khamenei%20signalled%20that%20Iran%20would%20retaliate%20directly%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20see%20avenging%20his%20blood%20our%20duty%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20happened%20on%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Republic.%20He%20said%20Israel%20had%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20receiving%20%26quot%3Ba%20severe%20punishment%2C%26quot%3B%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20Iranian%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20newly%20elected%20president%2C%20Masoud%20Pezeshkian%2C%20the%20foreign%20ministry%2C%20the%20Guards%20and%20Iran's%20mission%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20also%20said%20openly%20that%20Iran%20would%20retaliate%20against%20Israel%20and%20that%20it%20had%20a%20right%20to%20defend%20itself%20against%20a%20transgression%20on%20its%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20and%20the%20regional%20forces%20it%20backs%20--%20Hamas%2C%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%2C%20the%20Houthis%20in%20Yemen%20and%20multiple%20militias%20in%20Iraq%20--%20form%20what%20they%20call%20the%20%26quot%3Baxis%20of%20resistance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaders%20of%20those%20groups%20were%20in%20Tehran%20for%20the%20inauguration%20of%20Pezeshkian%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaniyeh%20was%20assassinated%20at%20about%202%20am%20(local%20time)%2C%20after%20attending%20the%20ceremony%20and%20meeting%20with%20Khamenei.%20The%20killing%20shocked%20Iranian%20officials%2C%20who%20described%20it%20as%20crossing%20red%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NYT%2C%20it%20was%20a%20humiliating%20security%20breach%20for%20Iran%2C%20which%20is%20eager%20to%20project%20strength%20but%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20prevent%20Israel%20from%20carrying%20out%20covert%20operations%20on%20its%20soil.%20The%20embarrassment%20was%20compounded%20by%20Haniyeh's%20prominence%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20other%20allies%2C%20and%20that%20he%20was%20attacked%20at%20a%20highly%20secure%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20guesthouse%20on%20a%20day%20of%20heightened%20security%20in%20the%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20reported%20citing%20analysts%20that%20Tehran%20sees%20retaliation%20as%20necessary%20for%20both%20avenging%20the%20killing%20of%20Haniyeh%20but%20also%20as%20deterrence%20against%20Israel%20killing%20other%20powerful%20enemies%2C%20like%20Hezbollah%20leader%20Hassan%20Nasrallah%2C%20or%20General%20Ismail%20Qaani%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20the%20Quds%20Forces%20who%20oversees%20the%20militant%20groups%20outside%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIran%20likely%20believes%20it%20has%20no%20choice%20other%20than%20retaliating%20to%20deter%20further%20Israeli%20attacks%2C%20defend%20its%20sovereignty%2C%20and%20preserve%20its%20credibility%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20its%20regional%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ali%20Vaez%2C%20the%20Iran%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Crisis%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and