fficials%20who%20complete%20three%20years%20on%20or%20before%20October%2031%2C%20for%20Maharashtra%2C%20the%20date%20is%20November%2030%2C%20and%20it%20is%20December%2031%20for%20Jharkhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20without%20an%20elected%20government%20for%20over%20six%20years%20and%20the%20last%20Assembly%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20December%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20week%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20will%20also%20complete%20five%20years%20as%20a%20Union%20Territory.%20On%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20was%20bifurcated%20into%20two%20Union%20Territories%20and%20its%20special%20status%20under%20Article%20370%20was%20removed.%20Since%20then%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20administered%20by%20the%20lieutenant%20governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20has%20also%20recently%20amended%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019%2C%20giving%20sweeping%20powers%20to%20the%20lieutenant%20governor%20in%20the%20Union%20Territory.%20The%20amendments%20are%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20Territory%20model%2C%20where%20the%20elected%20government%20has%20little%20authority%20over%20bureaucracy%20and%20many%20powers%20are%20vested%20in%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20parties%20have%20reacted%20strongly%20to%20the%20Centre's%20move%20and%20termed%20it%20%26quot%3Banti-democratic%26quot%3B.%20They%20allege%20that%20giving%20sweeping%20powers%20to%20the%20LG%20will%20make%20the%20elected%20government%20a%20rubber%20stamp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20visit%20to%20Srinagar%20in%20June%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20announced%20that%20Assembly%20elections%20would%20be%20held%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20soon%20and%20statehood%20would%20also%20be%20restored.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722448860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-05%2F6fjeb3ho_voting-generic_625x300_12_May_19.jpg%22%2C%22or