concept%20by%202025%20due%20to%20data%20quality%20issues%2C%20rising%20costs%2C%20and%20unclear%20business%20value.%20Despite%20early%20adopters%20experiencing%20benefits%20like%20revenue%20increases%20and%20productivity%20improvements%2C%20significant%20costs%20and%20risks%20have%20posed%20challenges%20for%20organizations%20investing%20in%20GenAI%20business%20models.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2F30-of-gen-ai-projects-will-be-dumped-by-the-end-of-2025-due-to-these-reasons-gartner%2Farticleshow%2F112170259.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20110%20km%20Long%20River%20Was%20Left%20To%20Die%2C%20Until%20an%20IAS%20Officer%20Helped%20Revive%20It%20in%206%20Months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERoughly%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Sot%20river%20%E2%80%93%20a%20tributary%20of%20the%20mighty%20Ganges%20%E2%80%93%20was%20a%20lifeline%20for%20the%20residents%20of%20the%20Sambhal%20district%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20with%20farmers%20depending%20on%20its%20water%20for%20irrigating%20their%20lush%20green%20paddy%20and%20peppermint%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20river%20that%20passes%20through%2071%20%3Cem%3Egram%20panchayats%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20five%20development%20blocks%20disappeared%20from%20the%20district%20due%20to%20large-scale%20encroachment%20and%20neglect.%20In%202022%2C%20when%20the%20newly-appointed%20district%20magistrate%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%20visited%20the%20field%2C%20he%20found%20there%20was%20hardly%20any%20water%20in%20the%20river.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20that%20the%20river%20was%20practically%20non-existent.%20We%20could%20only%20see%20small%20%3Cem%3Epuliya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(culverts)%20that%20were%20once%20made%20over%20the%20river.%20At%20several%20points%2C%20farmers%20had%20started%20growing%20crops%20considering%20it%20to%20be%20vacant%20land.%20The%20streak%20of%20the%20river%20was%20not%20completely%20connected%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20some%20places%2C%20the%20area%20was%20covered%20in%20small%20puddles.%20The%20river%20was%20encroached%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20it%20lost%20its%20path%20of%20natural%20flow%20downstream.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20nearby%20areas%20would%20remain%20waterlogged%20during%20monsoon.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Sot%20river%20acted%20as%20a%20natural%20drainage%20system%20for%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20the%20groundwater%20table%20had%20drastically%20reduced%20in%20the%20area%20as%20farmers%20became%20dependent%20on%20borewells%2C%20which%20further%20exacerbated%20the%20water%20problem%20in%20the%20region.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20hand%20pumps%2C%20as%20deep%20as%2050%20feet%2C%20started%20becoming%20non-functional%20because%20of%20the%20receding%20water%20table%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Manish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22When%20former%20district%20magistrate%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%20visited%20the%20field%2C%20he%20found%20there%20was%20hardly%20any%20water%20in%20the%20river.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359110%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhen%20former%20district%20magistrate%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%20visited%20the%20field%2C%20he%20found%20hardly%20any%20water%20in%20the%20river.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F357468%2Fias-officer-revive-water-table-cdo-varanasi-himanshu-nagpal-rainwater-harvesting-river-rejuvenation-groundwater-recharge%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20the%20IAS%20officer%20decided%20to%20rejuvenate%20the%20river%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20conversation%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20shares%20how%20the%20district%20administration%20revived%20the%20river%20to%20its%20old%20glory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20masterplan%20behind%20the%20river%20rejuvenation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpearheaded%20by%20Manish%2C%20the%20Sambhal%20district%20conducted%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20length%20of%20the%20river.%20The%20results%20showed%20that%20the%20Sot%20river%2C%20which%20appeared%20to%20be%20non-existent%2C%20was%20actually%20a%20110%20km%20long%20stretch%20starting%20from%20the%20Amroha%20district%20in%20the%20North%20and%20flowing%20towards%20Budaun%20in%20the%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20the%20administration%20conducted%20a%20survey%20to%20understand%20the%20natural%20alignment%20of%20the%20river.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20physical%20demarcation%20of%20the%20region%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20the%20river.%20The%20third%20step%20was%20to%20clear%20the%20illegal%20encroachments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20major%20challenges%20was%20to%20remove%20the%20encroachments%20along%20the%20river.%20Using%20the%20revenue%20land%20records%2C%20we%20understood%20that%20there%20were%20huge%20encroachments%20on%20the%20river%20area%20which%20had%20become%20flat%20at%20some%20points.%20Although%20there%20was%20no%20permanent%20construction%2C%20people%20started%20using%20it%20to%20grow%20crops.%20As%20it%20was%20illegal%20usage%2C%20we%20sought%20the%20help%20of%20the%20revenue%20land%20records%20team%20to%20clear%20encroachments%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Manish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20step%20was%20desilting%20of%20the%20river%20to%20remove%20fine%20silt%20and%20sediment%20collected%20in%20the%20river%20and%20restore%20it%20to%20its%20natural%20capacity.%20As%20part%20of%20this%2C%20the%20district%20administration%20roped%20in%20MGNREGA%20(Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act)%20workers%20to%20clean%20and%20dig%20the%20riverbed%20afresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarted%20in%20December%202022%2C%20the%20project%20was%20completed%20in%20six%20months%20by%20June%202023.%20During%20the%20last%20monsoon%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F348157%2Fmanganga-river-solapur-rejuvenation-efforts-vaijinath-ghongade-awarded-book-parikrama-mangangechi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20river%20captured%20the%20rainwater%20and%20was%20revived%20to%20its%20old%20glory%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20region%20was%20also%20free%20from%20waterlogging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20district%20administration%20roped%20in%20MGNREGA%20workers%20to%20clean%20and%20dig%20the%20riverbed%20afresh.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-1-1722402513-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359109%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20district%20administration%20roped%20MGNREGA%20workers%20to%20clean%20and%20dig%20the%20riverbed%20afresh.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20river%20has%20a%20catchment%20area.%20The%20natural%20flow%20of%20water%20in%20an%20area%20will%20be%20towards%20the%20river%2C%20so%20runoff%20water%20from%20nearby%20areas%20flows%20in%20that%20direction.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F355522%2Fwater-hero-rambabu-tiwari-mann-ki-baat-bundelkhand-drought-pond-revival-jal-mitra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIf%20the%20flow%20is%20hindered%2C%20then%20water%20gets%20logged%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20area%20but%20this%20time%2C%20this%20water%20was%20directed%20towards%20Sot%2C%E2%80%9D%20Manish%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20development%20was%20also%20followed%20by%20a%20massive%20plantation%20drive%20along%20the%20river%20bank.%20As%20many%20as%2010%2C000%20bamboo%20saplings%20were%20planted%20to%20prevent%20future%20soil%20erosion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaintaining%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20restored%20glory%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20project%20completion%2C%20it%20was%20observed%20that%20the%20seasonal%20Sot%20river%20received%20ample%20water%20in%20the%20monsoon%20and%20remained%20rejuvenated%20for%20the%20next%20two%20and%20a%20half%20months.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20project%2C%20several%20micro%20check%20dams%20were%20also%20built%20on%20the%20river%20to%20slow%20the%20runoff%20in%20the%20channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20this%20work%20was%20lauded%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20his%20monthly%20radio%20programme%20%E2%80%98Mann%20Ki%20Baat%E2%80%99%20in%20September%202023.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20proved%20to%20be%20very%20encouraging%20for%20all%20the%20officials%20and%20%3Cem%3Egram%20panchayats%3C%2Fem%3E%20associated%20with%20the%20project.%20Inspired%20by%20this%2C%20the%20districts%20of%20Amroha%20and%20Budaun%20also%20undertook%20the%20project%20of%20reviving%20the%20Sot%20river%20downstream%20and%20upstream%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Manish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Within%20six%20months%2C%20the%20district%20administration%20revived%20the%20river%20to%20its%20old%20glory.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-3-1722403565-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-359113%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWithin%20six%20months%2C%20the%20district%20administration%20revived%20the%20river%20to%20its%20old%20glory.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManish%20credits%20the%20success%20of%20the%20project%20to%20the%20local%20people%2C%20%3Cem%3Egram%20panchayats%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20MGNREGA%20workers%2C%20and%20district%20officials.%20In%20June%202024%2C%20he%20was%20transferred%20to%20Saharanpur%20district%20but%20this%20did%20not%20affect%20the%20success%20of%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERam%20Ashish%2C%20the%20District%20Development%20Officer%20of%20Sambhal%2C%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20keep%20monitoring%20for%20encroachments%20and%20ensure%20that%20the%20river%20remains%20rejuvenated.%20Post%20monsoon%2C%20the%20soil%20erodes%20into%20the%20river.%20So%2C%20we%20are%20working%20on%20a%20plan%20to%20organise%20desiltation%20and%20continue%20the%20work%20started%20by%20Manish%20sir.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20while%20some%20downstream%20areas%20currently%20have%20water%2C%20they%20expect%20to%20see%20the%20river%20filled%20to%20the%20brim%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20when%20it%20rains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20IAS%20Manish%20was%20reached%20out%20to%20by%20residents%20of%20Saharanpur%20to%20replicate%20the%20work%20seeing%20the%20success%20of%20the%20project%20in%20Sambhal%20district.%20%E2%80%9CSaharanpur%20has%20several%20seasonal%20rivers%20such%20as%20Kali%20and%20Hindon%20rivers.%20They%20originate%20from%20Shivaliks%20and%20pass%20through%20the%20district.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20their%20area%20has%20reduced%20in%20size.%20We%20aim%20to%20work%20on%20these%20rivers%20next%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Manish%20believes%20that%20the%20administration%20can%20only%20play%20the%20role%20of%20a%20facilitator%2C%20but%20it%20is%20only%20when%20the%20community%20becomes%20the%20protector%20of%20its%20rivers%20that%20they%20can%20remain%20rejuvenated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Manish%2C%20the%20Sot%20river%20rejuvenation%20project%20during%20his%20tenure%20in%20Sambhal%20was%20extremely%20fulfilling.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20project%20was%20very%20close%20to%20my%20heart.%20Projects%20such%20as%20river%20rejuvenation%20take%20a%20backseat%20as%20they%20are%20not%20always%20a%20priority%20among%20other%20routine%20works.%20But%20if%20we%20do%20not%20rejuvenate%20these%20rivers%2C%20people%20will%20face%20the%20brunt%20of%20a%20water%20crisis.%20Thankfully%2C%20the%20State%20Government%20has%20also%20been%20actively%20focusing%20on%20the%20environment%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F230547%2Fias-hero-kalyani-river-cleanup-uttar-pradesh-lockdown-jobs-methods-workers-inspiring-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereviving%20water%20bodies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20establishing%20Amrit%20Sarovar%20projects%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Khushi%20Arora%3B%20All%20photos%3A%20Ram%20Ashish.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722426607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Friver-2-1722402541.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D359103%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sot%20River%2C%20once%20the%20lifeline%20of%20Sambhal%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20lost%20its%20natural%20flow%20due%20to%20decades%20of%20encroachment.%20Here's%20how%20IAS%20Manish%20Bansal%2C%20along%20with%20officials%20and%20locals%2C%20revived%20the%20110-km%20stretch%2C%20restoring%20water%20flow%20and%20eliminating%20waterlogging.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F359103%2Fias-officer-sot-river-revival-rejuvenation-project-sambhal-uttar-pradesh-manish-bansal-mgnrega-gram-panchayat-monsoon-waterlogging%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rules%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20jettisoned%20after%20Hamas%20leader%20killed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722422700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F07%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-hamas-leader-ismail-haniyeh_66433